### [1/10] src\phonebook\__init__.py  (modules: phonebook)

## Root cause
The module cannot be imported because the package structure is incorrect - the `__init__.py` file is located in `src\phonebook\__init__.py` but Python expects it to be in the parent directory to make the `phonebook` package importable. The import paths in the `__init__.py` file are also incorrect, referencing `src.phonebook` instead of just `phonebook`.

## Fix type
WRONG_IMPORT

## Action
Move the `src\phonebook\__init__.py` file to `phonebook\__init__.py` (remove the `src` directory) and update the import paths in the `__init__.py` file to remove the `src.` prefix from all imports.

## Confidence
HIGH

## Notes
This is a common Python packaging mistake where the project structure doesn't match Python's import expectations. The user should also ensure they're running Python from the correct directory (likely the parent of the `src` directory) and that the `src` directory is in their Python path if they want to keep the current structure.

